data.description: Employs public health, epidemiology, medical anthropology, and global public health sources to illustrate the current and future effects of climate change on health from a cross-cultural, global perspective. Critically engage with health disparities with potential solutions or mitigations to the multiple public health crises created by climate change, from possible adaptations to more radical forms of community empowerment and social justice.
data.title: CLIMATE CHANGE AND HEALTH DISPARITIES
